- Powered by [Duet Date Picker](https://github.com/duetds/date-picker), the open source version of Duet Design System’s accessible date picker
- Inherits all the built-in accessibility features of Duet Date Picker plus additional optimisations made available through custom CSS theming
- Date picker calendar dates are styled to clearly indicate state whether selected, active or disabled, and considers focus styling
- The user interacts with the calendar button to toggle the popup panel – consistently whether using mouse, touch or keyboard. To hide the panel the user may toggle the button again, choose a date or press the ‘Esc’ key.
- Focus moves to the popup panel when shown
- Keyboard support includes calendar date navigation using keyboard arrow keys
- When the popup panel closes, focus returns to the button that originally toggled the panel
- An indicator outline appears around all buttons when focused
- The text input, text, calendar button, popup panel, selects and date buttons are visible in Windows High Contrast Mode (WHCM). Calendar date focus styling is also visible in WHCM.
